            <div type="translation">
                <p>Brothers, I urge you, as foreigners and exiles, to abstain from sinful (desires).</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>The inscription is from Peter's Epistle I, 2:11: Ἀγαπητοί, παρακαλῶ ὡς παροίκους καὶ παρεπιδήμους ἀπέχεσθαι τῶν σαρκικῶν ἐπιθυμιῶν. However, the incipit Ἀδελφοί, παρακαλῶ ὑμᾶς, originates from Paul's epistles. Text reconstruction was based on the photographs of the Department of Antiquities, Cyprus. </p>
            </div>
